# How to look up user details

- Once you have logged into the portal.
- On the left hand side  menu - select ‘User Details’
- Enter the username, email address or phone number  in the box below, then press ‘Find user details’
  The details should then appear underneath for the selected user.

<img src="/images/search_for_user_details.png" alt= "Enter the user details">
- You have the ability to search via username or phone number.
<img src="/images/search_via_username.png" alt= "Enter the username">
<br>
<img src="/images/search_via_number.png" alt= "Enter the user's phone number">

## How to check if an organisation is already on the allow list
*Use this before adding a new organisation to avoid duplicates.*

- Sign in to the Super Admin portal and go to Allow list, then select 'Start'
  <img src="/images/give_org_access.png" alt= "Give an organisation access to GovWifi">

- Use the organisation name search on the allow list start page. Check whether the correct organisation is on the list.

<img src="/images/org_allow_list_search.png" alt= "Give an organisation access to GovWifi">

- Only add a new organisation or domain if it does not already exist.

  <img src="/images/allow_org_admin_platform.png" alt="Enter the full name of the organisation">
- You will be notified once the organisation has been successfully added

  <img src="/images/custom_org_added_allow_list.png" alt="confirmation message, that the organisation has been added">